<div class="detail-container">
  <div class="detail-header">
    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-container">
    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>General Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>What is ThinkHub Academic Portal?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>ThinkHub Academic Portal is a comprehensive Learning Management System (LMS) designed to facilitate online education. It provides tools for course management, academic class scheduling, attendance tracking, grading, certificate generation, and content publishing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>How do I navigate through the portal?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>You can use the sidebar menu on the left to navigate through different sections of the portal. The Dashboard provides an overview of your activities, while specific sections like Courses, Academic Classes, etc. allow you to manage those aspects of your learning experience.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>Is my data secure on the platform?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes, we take data security very seriously. The platform employs industry-standard encryption and security measures to protect your personal information and academic records. All communication with our servers is encrypted, and we regularly update our security protocols.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Courses and Academic Classes</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>How do I enroll in a course?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>To enroll in a course, navigate to the Courses section from the sidebar. Browse available courses and click on the one you're interested in. On the course detail page, you'll find an "Enroll" button. Click it to register for the course.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>What's the difference between a course and an academic class?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>A course represents the subject or topic of study (e.g., "Introduction to Programming"), while an academic class represents a specific scheduled instance of teaching that course (e.g., "Intro to Programming - Fall 2025, Monday/Wednesday").</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>How do I create a new academic class?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>To create a new academic class, navigate to the Academic Classes section from the sidebar and click the "New Academic Class" button. Fill in the required information in the form and submit it. Note that only instructors and administrators have permission to create new classes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Grades and Certificates</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>How are grades calculated?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Grades are calculated based on your performance in assignments, quizzes, exams, and other assessments as defined by the instructor. Each component may have different weightage, which is usually specified in the course syllabus.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>When do I receive my certificate?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Certificates are typically issued upon successful completion of a course. The criteria for "successful completion" may vary by course but usually includes achieving a passing grade and completing all required components of the course.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>How can I download or share my certificate?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>You can access your certificates in the Certificates section. Each certificate has options to download it as a PDF or share it directly via email or social media. The certificates also have a unique QR code that can be used to verify authenticity.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Blogs and Content</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>Who can publish blogs on the platform?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Instructors and administrators can publish blogs on the platform. These blogs can be used for announcements, educational content, or other relevant information. If you're a student interested in contributing, please contact your instructor or an administrator.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>How do I create a new blog post?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>To create a new blog post, navigate to the Blogs section from the sidebar and click the "New Blog" button. Fill in the title, content, and optionally add a featured image. Use the rich text editor to format your content and add multimedia elements.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>Can I comment on blog posts?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes, you can comment on blog posts to engage in discussions. Comments are moderated to ensure a respectful and constructive environment. To comment on a blog post, scroll to the bottom of the post and use the comment form provided.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Technical Support</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>What browsers are supported?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>ThinkHub Academic Portal supports all modern browsers including Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge. For the best experience, we recommend keeping your browser updated to the latest version.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>I found a bug or have a feature request. Where can I report it?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We appreciate your feedback! Please contact our support team at support@thinkhub.edu with details about the bug you encountered or your feature suggestion. Include screenshots and steps to reproduce the issue if applicable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          <h3>How can I reset my password?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>If you forgot your password, click on the "Forgot Password?" link on the login page. Enter your registered email address to receive a password reset link. Follow the instructions in the email to create a new password.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

